This paper deals with the complexity of a computational problem, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The problem involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as possible sub-categories. The paper also involves probability and information theory, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
